<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-03-0873 </DOCNO><TEXT>In the light of the ratification of the homogeneous European Act, twoessays of the basic problems in the framework of European and Germanenvironmental policy are quoted and discussed. The thesis is represented,that European environmental policy can replace neither national nor regionalenvironmental policy. Environmental policy in Europe must, on the contrary,be a functionally graded and organised system of action, in which, onseveral levels, complementary but independent decisions are taken. Thesecond essay concentrates on the optimal decision level, which must befound in view of efficiency factors. (HSCH).</TEXT></DOC>